to the editor re a teacher 's lasting impressions by d t max op ed jan 22 mr max 's observations and conclusions concerning teachers are commendable we in the profession know all too well that teaching when it succeeds is as much personal as structural yet much of our training and assessing of teachers remains primarily structural we need a new educational paradigm in which the personal and subsequently the inspirational are the primary focus of sound education larry hoffner new york jan 22 2001 the writer is a new york city high school teacher

